Gradually, with a slavish clockwork immunity to alcohol, Luana drained the bottom stretch of a beer. Now ignoring the males of the expedition, Luana compared the girls, wondering what they hoped to find in the guts of nowhere.
At the far extreme of the bar was General Luana, skin like satchel leather, watching the white boys drink. There were four males in the group, the other half consisting of women.
